===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[quotation]] [[mark]]}} ''(normally plural)''

# {{UK}} One of a pair of [[quotation marks]] used to [[denote]] a [[quotation]] in [[writing]]. The [[symbol]] used at the beginning of the quotation ''("[[opening quotation mark]]")'' is usually <big>'''[[“]]'''</big> ("[[open inverted commas]]") or <big>'''[[‘]]'''</big> ("[[open inverted comma]]"), and the symbol at the end ''("[[closing quotation mark]]") is <big>'''[[”]]'''</big> ("[[close inverted commas]]") or <big>'''[[’]]'''</big> ("[[close inverted comma]]").
# {{North America}} One of a pair of quotation marks used to denote a quotation in writing. The same symbol is usually used at both the beginning and the end of the quotation, which is usually the  "[[double quote]]" symbol <big>'''[["]]'''</big>, although the "[[single quote]]" symbol <big>'''[[']] '''</big> is sometimes used, especially to denote a quotation within a quotation.

